Canadian Airlines Internationalsaid it agreed to purchase six Boeing Co 767-300ER (extendedrange) aircraft, and options on eight more, for 1.6 billionCanadian dlrs, including spare parts and training.    Delivery will begin in April 1988 and run through April1989, the company said.    The airline said it plans to finance the new aircraft bymeans of oeprating leases. Canadian Airlines was recentlyformed through the merger of Canadian Pacific Airlines andPacific Western Airlines. Reuter&#3;